{
  "texts": [
    "Preserving a record of every person who has come into contact with humans or animals that have been confirmed to have Mpox is essential.",
    "Individuals should also be instructed to take their temperature two times a day and be watched for the onset of symptoms for 3 weeks after the last known exposure.",
    "Significant improvements in compliance processes can be achieved by providing personal supervision, instruction, checklists, feedback, and enough time for donning and doffing.",
    "These measures will help to greatly control the Mpox outbreak (Cices et al., 2023).",
    "Currently, the FDA has licensed two antiviral medications, Tecovirimat (TPOXX or ST-246) and Brincidofovir (CMX001 or Tembexa), as alternative treatment for those infected with Mpox."
  ]
}